rComments: Be sure to set up your online assignment profile early, because if you have technical difficulties, the response you will get will bear an overwhelming attitude of "why are you bothering me?". Additionally, the absolute most difficult content happened in the two weeks following course evaluation, while the easiest was dragged on early for weeks.

Very fair teacher who tests on her slides and is easy enough to get a good grade in. The midterms are very easy although there is a lot of material to study. Final was much harder and very long. No need to show up to her classes, just study her slides. Lectures are unbearably long and boring, she is pleasant and friendly enough if help is needed.

Very easy class. You can learn the entire class directly from the textbook and online assignments. The prof's lectures are very good and can also teach you everything if you're not using the textbook.   The prof doesnt use a mic and sometimes sounds like Frau in Austin Powers. It scares me.

Don't need to show up to lectures at all, very boring and monotone reads directly off slides longest lectures you will ever attend. That being said, slides are well done, read slides and  gives in class exam questions on lecture tools. Just read slides and you will get general idea of class but for a great mark read textbook.
Reads off slides but provides lots of practice questions. Very fair teacher especially if you come to class.
